## 📋 Overview

**Feature:** AMS Findings Panel on Farmer Dashboard
**Module:** Farmer Dashboard — AMS Findings Panel
**Round:** Round 1
**Environment:** CENTEST
**Application:** Basic Income Support for Sustainability (BISS)
**Created by:** Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
**Date:** 28-Apr-2026

**Context:**
The AMS (Area Monitoring System) uses satellite imagery to monitor land parcels declared under
BISS. When a potential non-compliance is detected on a parcel (e.g. Artificial Surface, crop
mismatch, Agricultural Activity), the system generates a Red AMS finding for that herd.
These findings appear on the Farmer Dashboard as an AMS Findings panel, prompting the farmer
or their agent to respond before the 8 July 2026 deadline.

**Important — Date Message Change from Last Year:**
The deadline message displayed in the AMS Findings panel has been updated for 2026.
All scenarios must verify the message reads the 2026 date — NOT last year’s deadline.

- Individual / Primary Partner message: “You have until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”
- Non-Primary Partner message: “The Primary Partner has until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications”

