### Query F — Find AMS Crop Mismatch Herds

**Source:** Query 79 from reference document
**Used for:** TC-AMS-01 additional test data — crop mismatch type AMS finding

**Audit note:**
`vweo_ams_inspected_land` holds the actual AMS satellite inspection results.
`fn_haserrorforapp(..., 1036, 'A')` checks for error code 1036 of AMS type ‘A’.
This gives herds where the crop declared on BISS application does not match
what AMS satellite inspection found — useful for verifying specific finding detail on panel.

```sql
-- Query 79 (adapted for 2026 — change herd number as needed)
-- Shows AMS crop mismatch between declared crop and AMS inspection finding
SELECT apl.app_year,
       apl.app_herd_no        AS applicant_herd_no,
       apl.parcel_id          AS parcel,
       apl.apl_sub_div_no     AS sub_div_no,
       pkbs_error_validation.fn_haserrorforapp(
           apl.app_year, apl.app_id, apl.aph_id, apl.apl_id, 1036, 'A'
       )                      AS incorrect_ams_stop_ind,
       apl.crp_desc           AS application_crop,
       ams.crop_found_eos     AS ams_crop_found_eos,
       ams.crop_found_inspectors AS ams_crop_found_inspectors,
       ams.inspection_date    AS ams_inspection_date
FROM vwbs_application_land apl
LEFT JOIN vweo_ams_inspected_land ams
    ON  apl.apl_lnu_id  = ams.lnu_id
    AND COALESCE(apl.apl_sub_div_no, -1) = COALESCE(ams.subdivision, -1)
    AND apl.app_herd_no = ams.inspected_herd
    AND apl.app_year    = ams.scheme_year
WHERE apl.app_year        = 2026
AND   apl.mde_abbrev      = 'I'
AND   apl.apl_deleted_ind = 'N'
AND   apl.app_herd_no     IN ('<HERD_NUMBER_HERE>')
GROUP BY apl.app_year, apl.app_id, apl.aph_id, apl.apl_id,
         ams.inspection_date, apl.app_herd_no, apl.parcel_id,
         apl.apl_sub_div_no, apl.crp_desc, ams.crop_found_eos,
         ams.crop_found_inspectors;
```

