## ⚠️ Key Notes for Development Team and Testers

### 1. Query Audit — Why Queries Were Combined

**Query 70 alone is insufficient for TC-AMS-01 precondition.**
`VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD` returns all AMS notified herds regardless of application status.
A Submitted herd (app_mde_code=4) would appear in results, violating the Pre-Submit precondition.
Correct approach: Join Q70 + Q87 + Q93 together as shown in Query A above.

**Query 74 title says “both AMS and PC” — confirmed correct.**
`lvt_abbrev` in `vwbs_land_validation` holds the finding type abbreviation.
`COUNT(DISTINCT lvt_abbrev) > 1` confirms more than one finding type exists for the same parcel.
`lvs_abbrev NOT IN ('E','V','W')` correctly excludes non-actionable finding statuses.

**Query 85 (`vwbs_ams_response`) — ams_round must be set to 1 not 5.**
The original document shows `ams_round = 5` — this was for a different round.
For Round 1 testing set `ams_round = 1`.

